---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import OrchestrationFlow from '../components/content/OrchestrationFlow.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="From content systems to AI systems"
  description="As AI models become easier to access, the advantage shifts to the organisations that can orchestrate knowledge, memory, judgement and execution. Editorial Intelligence is that layer."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">AI systems</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">From content systems<br />to AI systems</h1>
        <p class="hero-def mb-6">
          As AI models become easier to access, the advantage shifts to the organisations that can orchestrate knowledge, memory, judgement and execution.
        </p>
        <p class="t-body leading-relaxed">
          Most organisations are not short of AI tools. They are short of connected intelligence. Research, customer stories, event conversations, sales feedback and market signals already exist across the business — but they rarely connect into a system that AI can reliably use. Editorial Intelligence creates that system.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Core model -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-3">The orchestration model</h2>
        <p class="section-intro mb-10">Editorial Intelligence sits between what the organisation knows and what AI can help produce. That middle layer — the orchestration layer — is where memory, frameworks, judgement and execution connect.</p>
        <OrchestrationFlow />
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Why this matters now -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">Why this matters now</h2>
        <p class="section-intro mb-8">The early phase of generative AI focused on models and prompts. The next phase is about systems. Organisations need ways to connect fragmented knowledge, preserve context and turn evidence into repeatable outputs without losing editorial judgement.</p>

        <div class="card-grid">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Models are becoming accessible</div>
            <p class="card-body">Many teams can now access strong AI models. The difference is not simply which model they use, but what knowledge, context and workflow sits around it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Memory becomes a moat</div>
            <p class="card-body">AI is only as useful as the information it can work with. Editorial Intelligence gives organisations a way to turn scattered insight into structured, reusable memory.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-title">Orchestration creates value</div>
            <p class="card-body">The value is in deciding what to use, how to combine it, what to produce and how learning feeds back into the system. That is an editorial function, not a technical one.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- B2B relevance -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">Why this is especially relevant for B2B content</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>B2B organisations already generate valuable evidence through research, events, customer stories and practitioner conversations. But too often, those assets are treated as one-off campaigns. Editorial Intelligence makes them reusable, connected and usable by AI-supported workflows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="example-list">
          <div class="example-item">
            <span class="example-icon">→</span>
            <p>A research report becomes articles, sales narratives, social posts, video scripts and customer-facing tools — not a single launch.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="example-item">
            <span class="example-icon">→</span>
            <p>Event conversations become market signals and future thought leadership rather than recaps that nobody reads.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="example-item">
            <span class="example-icon">→</span>
            <p>Customer stories become proof points across campaigns, sales enablement and product narratives — connected rather than isolated.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="example-item">
            <span class="example-icon">→</span>
            <p>Performance data shows which narratives are resonating and should be developed further, feeding directly back into the evidence base.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Where agents fit -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-4">Where agents fit</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Agentic AI is not just about chatbots answering questions. It is about AI systems that can complete tasks across workflows. In editorial and marketing teams, agents can help identify signals, brief content, adapt assets, recommend next actions and maintain knowledge bases — but only when the knowledge layer underneath them is structured.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="agent-stack">
          <div class="agent-item">
            <div class="agent-label">Signal capture agent</div>
            <p class="agent-desc">Captures useful material from research, events, customer calls and performance data — and routes it into the organisational memory layer.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="agent-connector" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
          <div class="agent-item">
            <div class="agent-label">Briefing agent</div>
            <p class="agent-desc">Turns stored evidence into structured briefs for articles, campaigns, videos or sales assets — with the organisation's narrative logic built in.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="agent-connector" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
          <div class="agent-item">
            <div class="agent-label">Reuse agent</div>
            <p class="agent-desc">Identifies where existing evidence can support new content or campaigns, reducing duplication and increasing the return on original research.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="agent-connector" aria-hidden="true">↓</div>
          <div class="agent-item">
            <div class="agent-label">Performance agent</div>
            <p class="agent-desc">Tracks what worked and feeds learning back into the memory layer — so the system improves with each cycle rather than starting again.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p class="agent-note mt-6">Each agent is only as useful as the knowledge it has access to. This is where Editorial Intelligence becomes the foundation, not just the methodology.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Closing statement -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <div class="closing-block">
          <p class="closing-lead">Editorial Intelligence is the knowledge and orchestration layer for AI-enabled content systems.</p>
          <p class="closing-sub mb-6">It connects what the organisation knows, what the market is signalling, what customers are saying, what AI can help produce, and what performance data teaches next.</p>
          <p class="closing-sub">This is how content moves from isolated production to a learning system.</p>
          <div class="closing-links mt-8">
            <a href="/intelligence" class="closing-link">What is Editorial Intelligence? →</a>
            <a href="/frameworks" class="closing-link">Frameworks →</a>
            <a href="/narratives/agentic-ai" class="closing-link">Agentic AI narrative →</a>
            <a href="/work" class="closing-link">Work with me →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero-def {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  /* Why this matters cards */
  .card-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 640px) {
    .card-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .card-title {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .card-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* B2B examples */
  .example-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 5px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .example-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .example-item:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .example-icon {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    padding-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .example-item p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Agent stack */
  .agent-stack {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .agent-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .agent-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .agent-desc {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .agent-connector {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.4;
    line-height: 2;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .agent-note {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Closing block */
  .closing-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .closing-lead {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1.8vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .closing-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .closing-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .closing-link {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 30%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: border-color 0.15s;
  }

  .closing-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
  }
</style>
